<p>Viewing deliverable status</p><p>Review the progress being made on the deliverables for your
	 release. 
  </p> 
	  
		<ul> 
		   
			  To appear on the Deliverables
				Dashboard, an asset must be identified as an asset and be linked to a work
				package. 
			  
		   
		 
	 </ul> 
	  
		<p> Using the Deliverables Dashboard,
		  you can easily identify the status and progress being made on the deliverables
		  impacted for the releases of your product. 
		</p> 
	  
	  
		 
		   Select your product from the drop-down at the top of the
			 Dashboard tab. 
		   
		   The Dashboard is refreshed and shows status information
			 for the selected product. 
		   
		 
		
		  In the Deliverables area, place your cursor over the status bar to
			 see the rate of completion for the deliverables impacted for the release.
		  
		
		
		  Click a release name to see the list of impacted deliverables and
			 their rate of completion.
		  
		
		
		  Click a deliverable's name to see the iterations in which the work
			 is scheduled for the deliverable.
		  
		
		
		  Click an iteration's name to see the work packages within the
			 iteration.
		  
		  The Iterations tab is displayed for the selected iteration.
		  
		
	  
	  
		<p> Progress details for the
		  deliverables are displayed. 
		</p> 
	  
  